<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3687] TimeCategory 10.minutes.ago zeros out the time</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3687</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; org.codehaus.groovy.runtime.TimeCategory
use ( TimeCategory ) {
   println 10.minutes.ago.format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;yyyyMMdd HH:mm:ss&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prints: &lt;tt&gt;20090818 00:00:00&lt;/tt&gt; &amp;lt;- Note that the time component has been reset to zero.  Conversely, &lt;tt&gt;10.minutes.from.now&lt;/tt&gt; works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll try to look into this but I&apos;ve left it unassigned for now.  I&apos;m not sure if someone else could resolve this more quickly than I could.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
