                            <comment id="14467468" author="tim_yates" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2009 05:20:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TimeDuration extends the Duration class, and overrides the getFrom method, but not the getAgo method&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For some reason (that I haven&apos;t had time to go into) the getAgo method of Duration has&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// SqlDate should not really care about these values but it seems to &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;remember&quot;&lt;/span&gt; them
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// so we clear them.
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// We &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; the adds first incase we get carry into the day field
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;inside it (and it then blanks the hour, minute, second and milisecond)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch introduces an override of getAgo inside TimeDuration that is a copy of the Duration method, minus these zeroing calls&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14467578" author="tomstrummer" created="Fri, 28 Aug 2009 13:16:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied patch &amp;amp; committed to trunk, r17471.  Note that I replaced the &apos;new java.sql.Date&apos; with cal.getTime() (the java.util.Date instance).  Added unit tests to DurationTest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TODO: additional tests &amp;amp; merge into 1.6.x branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14467510" author="tim_yates" created="Fri, 28 Aug 2009 16:50:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Note that I replaced the &apos;new java.sql.Date&apos; with cal.getTime() (the java.util.Date instance).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This could possibly be done for &quot;getAgo&quot; and &quot;getFrom&quot; in the Duration class as well&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
